parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
especially at low speeds
the power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power steering assistance
and there may be a burning smell or smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission system can cause the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle slows down or speeds up unexpectedly
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may not shift gears properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the engine to overheat, leading to further damage.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine RPMs fluctuate
the vehicle is unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering pump makes unusual noises
the power steering fluid leaks
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake light does not function
the brake light is dim or flickering
the brake light is not visible to other drivers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause the window to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The passenger side window does not roll down
the window motor fails to operate
the window becomes stuck in the "up" position
the window glass can potentially contact the door frame when closing
presenting a breakage hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and failure of the windshield can cause a loss of structural integrity, leading to potential safety risks, including the risk of ejection or airbag malfunction.
symptoms: Cracks in the windshield
often originating from small chips or stones
stress cracks
cracks that propagate rapidly
windshield failure without visible impact
cracks that occur without obvious reasons.
